><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/16/01 7:34:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: possibilities</span><hr size=1> Tudamorf said: <b>The motivation behind the TLC has NOTHING to do with farming or camping in general, so stop going back to those dead arguments</b><br>
<br>
I'm not the one going back to those dead arguments.  Someone else brought them up, and I am merely pointing out that they are, in fact, invalid.  People try to resurrect a dead horse, I'll beat it back into the ground.<br>
<br>
<b>Now, if every player were reasonable and willing to compromise with their peers, the high level farming issue wouldn't be nearly as great and TLC code wouldn't be high on the priority list. </b><br>
<br>
Agreed.  It all comes back to camp monopolization and an unwillingness to share.  If lower level players were more willing to invoke the PNP, and if the PNP could be enforced quickly and fairly when invoked...<br>
<br>
<br>
***<br>
<br>
BTW, the Quit-If-You're-60 crowd shouldn't be celebrating too much.  According to the following statement from Brad yesterday, it sounds as if a number of the low/mid level old world dungons will be converted to higher level dungeons.  How high remains to be seen, of course:<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>The reason I ask this is that as a high level player (60) I would love to have access to some high level dungeons that are only explored by one group at a time. This doesn't seem to happen because all the post 50 players are pretty much crowded into 3 or 4 zones. I guess what I'm asking is why do you continue to develop new mid level zones when a large majority of the current mid level zones never get used, while at the same time high levels are forced to fight in zones with 80 plus people. <br>
<br>
Nylak<br>
<br>
<b>In addition to making sure there are several high-level dungeons on Luclin, we also plan on converting some of the existing and underused older dungeons to high-level zones. We realize that it’s not just treasure, but also distance that can frustrate low and mid-level players and that some zones are just too far away. Around the time of Luclin’s release or soon after, several of these zones will be changed such that higher-level players are their target audience. </b></i><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upaldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/16/01 7:59:22 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: possibilities</span><hr size=1> I think with the introduction of the new level-based loot code, we need an additional 'slash' command.<br>
<br>
"/noexp"<br>
<br>
What this does is makes it so a player's character does not gain XPs from any encounter.<br>
<br>
It does not effect other characters in any way (meaning, that if a player is in "/noexp" mode and part of a group.. He still takes his 'share' of experience out of the group, but it just dissapears.<br>
<br>
(This prevents people from discriminating on people for the "/noexp" tag... i.e. "Yeah, you can join our group, but you gotta come /noexp for the first hour.")<br>
<br>
Also, they have to make it so that the '/noexp' tag does not intefear with anyone's resurections (meaning they still get back the exps for the Res).<br>
<br>
=-=-=-=-=-<br>
<br>
This tag would give people the option to be able to play their characters without worring about xps... This could be useful for many situations...<br>
<br>
* Some people enjoy a certain level range, and this lets them play EQ at a specific range/difficulty level.<br>
<br>
* Some people want to wait for friends to 'catch up' to them, but don't want to stop playing.<br>
<br>
* Some want to get a specific item in Warrens, or now Luclin.. and this will let them stay fighting in an area till they can get it.<br>
